# Keystatic GitHub Mode Configuration
# Documentation: https://keystatic.com/docs/github-mode
# IMPORTANT: You need a GitHub App (NOT GitHub OAuth App!)
# See SETUP_GITHUB_APP.md for complete instructions

# GitHub App credentials (from https://github.com/settings/apps)
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_app_client_id
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_app_client_secret

# Keystatic secret for signing session cookies
# Generate with: node scripts/generate-keystatic-secret.js
KEYSTATIC_SECRET=your_generated_secret_here

# GitHub App slug (the URL-friendly name of your GitHub App)
# Example: if your app URL is https://github.com/settings/apps/keystatic-cms-mysite
# then the slug is: keystatic-cms-mysite
NEXT_PUBLIC_KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_APP_SLUG=your-github-app-slug

# CRITICAL: Keystatic uses these exact environment variable names
# Do NOT rename them or use GITHUB_CLIENT_ID/GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET

# Quick Setup Instructions:
# 1. Create a GitHub App (NOT OAuth App!) at https://github.com/settings/apps/new
#    - See SETUP_GITHUB_APP.md for detailed step-by-step instructions
#    - Name: "Keystatic CMS - Your Site Name"
#
# 2. Configure the GitHub App:
#    - Homepage URL: https://your-domain.vercel.app
#    - Callback URL: https://your-domain.vercel.app/api/keystatic/github/oauth/callback
#    - Permissions: Repository Contents (Read and write)
#
# 3. Generate a client secret and copy it immediately
#
# 4. Install the GitHub App to your repository (Kapinoida/dcplaskett-portfolio-working)
#
# 5. Add ALL FOUR environment variables to Vercel:
#    - KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID
#    - KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET
#    - KEYSTATIC_SECRET
#    - NEXT_PUBLIC_KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_APP_SLUG
#    - Set for ALL environments (Production, Preview, Development)
#
# 6. Redeploy your application for changes to take effect
